The paper discusses the optimization of matrix-matrix multiplication, which is a fundamental operation in linear algebra and is used in various scientific fields. The focus is on sparse matrices, which are commonly used in electronic structure theory and low scaling correlated methods. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.MS (Mathematical Software), which deals with the development and optimization of mathematical software. The paper also discusses communication reduction algorithms and one-sided MPI communication, which are relevant to distributed computing (cs.DC) and parallel computing (cs.SC). The optimization of matrix-matrix multiplication involves numerical analysis (cs.NA) and data structures (cs.DS).
